commit.message: Support command playlistlength

Support range argument for listplaylist and listplaylistinfo

Adds two new functions:
- mpd_send_list_playlist_range
- mpd_send_list_playlist_range_meta

README.rst: refer to LICENSES directory, not COPYING

Closes https://github.com/MusicPlayerDaemon/libmpdclient/issues/115
increment version number to 2.23
release v2.22
use SPDX IDs, replacing the long copyright headers
Merge branch 'queue_save' of https://github.com/jcorporation/libmympdclient

meson.build: generate version.h in include/mpd/

This fixes a "version.h" conflict when used as a Meson subproject:
when the parent project also generates a "version.h", it is not clear
which one will be included.  We solve this by requiring the "mpd/"
prefix for libmpdclient.

See https://github.com/MusicPlayerDaemon/MPD/pull/1927
meson.build: move header installation rules to include/mpd/meson.build
README.rst: update minimum Meson version
meson.build: do not define _GNU_SOURCE with MSVC
status: add more casts to suppress narrowing warnings
song: fix pointer/bool mismatch
fix various narrowing warnings by adding explicit casts

.github/workflows/build.yml: add "action:build" for Windows

Without having any "action", BSFishy/meson-build fails with "Error:
Unknown Meson action:", d'oh!

.github/workflows/build.yml: remove "action:test" for Windows

Since unit tests are disabled on Windows (due to the lack of "check"),
"meson build" will simply do nothing.
.github/workflows/build.yml: add Windows build with MSVC instead of GCC
meson.build: remove -Wused-but-marked-unused because it triggers on assert()
meson.build: enable more GCC warnings
compiler.h: use "gnu_printf", fixing -Wsuggest-attribute=format
player, send: fix -Wdouble-promotion
meson.build: sort warning options
meson.build: use get_supported_arguments()

meson.build: use a minimal linker script for the --version-script test

Fixes linking with mold which gets unhappy if the linker script refers
to symbols which do not exist.

Closes https://github.com/MusicPlayerDaemon/libmpdclient/issues/114
meson.build: require Meosn 0.56, use get_supported_link_arguments()
build: remove unused build scripts

.github/workflows/build.yml: install the latest Meson version on Windows

Need at least 0.54.2 for the
https://github.com/mesonbuild/meson/issues/3672 fix

drop the unmaintained Vala bindings

Those have been added 11 years ago by commit
f20a299e3ee907ac8b0a0ebc01389f3954f89c6d, and received one trivial
patch 9 years ago and then were never touched again.  I have never
heard of anybody using them, and no new features have been added
there, which suggests nobody is using them.  So let's not pretend we
support Vala.

ierror: use FormatMessageA() instead of FormatMessage()

Just in case _UNICODE is defined.
increment version number to 2.22
